Keep your @butter{10%g} in the fridge.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{4} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add half the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @water{220%ml} and half the @chicken stock paste{20%g} and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{110%g} and pop a lid on the pan.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Stir the remaining garlic and @balsamic glaze{12%g} into the pan until combined.

Squish the tomatoes until they burst, then add the chicken stock paste, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{75%ml}.

Bring the sauce to a simmer and reduce until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and vigorously stir in the cold butter.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Stir the @fresh pesto{50%g} through the couscous and fluff up with a #fork{}.

Share the pesto couscous between your bowls, then top with the chicken and smashed tomato sauce.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} over the top to finish.

Enjoy!